ting is ignored for read-only databases.\n\n__Warning__: When this setting is enabled, undo and redo functionality is achieved through \"inverted\" SQLite statements, which are not guaranteed to work (e.g. another process has modified the same row, etc.)"},"sqliteViewer.doubleClickBehavior":{"type":"string","enum":["modal","vscode"],"enumDescriptions":["Modal Dialog","VS Code Editor"],"default":"modal","markdownDescription":"Controls the behavior when double-clicking on a cell in the table view.\n\n- **Modal Dialog**: Opens the row in an integrated modal dialog (default)\n- **VS Code Editor**: Opens the cell value in a separate VS Code editor tab (PRO feature)"}}},"commands":[{"command":"sqlite-viewer.addFileNestingPatterns","title":"Add SQLite File Nesting Patterns","category":"SQLite Viewer"},{"command":"sqlite-viewer.enterLicenseKey","title":"Activate License Key","category":"SQLite Viewer"},{"command":"sqlite-viewer.removeLicenseKey","title":"Deactivate License Key","category":"SQLite Viewer"},{"command":"sqlite-viewer.enterAccessToken","title":"Offline License Activation","category":"SQLite Viewer"},{"command":"sqlite-viewer.exportTable","title":"Export Table","category":"SQLite Viewer"}]},"scripts":{"clean":"rm -rf out && rm -rf sqlite-viewer-core/vscode/build","vscode:prepublish":"npm run $([ -z \"$VSCODE_EXT_SKIP_BUILD\" ] && echo build || echo compile:bin)","compile:ext":"npm run compile:ext:cp & npm run compile:ext:js & wait","compile:ext:cp":"cp -r node_modules/@vscode/codicons node_modules/codicons","compile:ext:js":"bun run scripts/esbuild.ts","compile:app":"cd sqlite-viewer-core && npm run build-vscode","compile:tjs":"cd sqlite-viewer-core && npm run build-tjs","compile:bin":"npm run compile:tjs && bun run scripts/bin.ts","compile":"$([ -n \"$DEV\" ] && npm run build:zig:bin || true) && npm run clean && npm run compile:bin && npm run compile:ext && npm run compile:app","build:zig:bin":"cd zig-build-txiki && zig@14 build --summary all","build:zig:matrix